Initial version of organized BooleanRingsCategory file.

Following the structure of Cubical.Categories.Instances.CommRings, defines:

1. BooleanRingsCategory - universe-polymorphic category of Boolean rings
   (objects: BooleanRing ℓ, morphisms: BoolHom = CommRingHom on underlying CommRings)

2. ForgetfulBooleanRing→Set - forgetful functor to SET

3. BoolRingIsoIsoCatIso - Iso between BoolRingEquiv and CatIso

4. isUnivalentBooleanRingsCategory₀ - univalence (at ℓ-zero)
   Uses J-based approach from StuffFromStoneAboutBAs

5. TerminalBooleanRing - terminal object (Unit with trivial BR structure)

6. Fibered product of Boolean rings - lifts CommRing fibered product
   by proving idempotency holds componentwise

7. PullbackBooleanRingsCategory - pullbacks via fibered product

8. LimitsBooleanRingsCategory - general limits
   Takes limit in SET via forgetful functor, equips with pointwise
   BooleanRing structure (0, 1, +, ·, -, CommRing axioms + idempotency)

All definitions compile and type-check successfully.
